Maintain/improve technical knowledge by attending educational workshops, reviewing professional publications, obtaining applicable certifications etc.;
Act as a mentor to software engineers, takes ownership of a product
Performs other duties as directedQualifications
 University Degree (Equivalent to a Bachelor’s degree), preferably in Computer Science, Information Technology, Mathematics or a technically related discipline and 5+ years in software systems engineering;
Extensive development experience with Java programming language;
Experience in software development tools (versioning systems, bug tracking tools) and processes (continuous integration, automatic testing);
Affinity and/or experience in smartcards, RFID, mobile, secure systems, data processing, networking is preferred;
Affinity/experience with cyber security and cryptography is to your advantage;
Previous experience in customer facing roles, requiring both technical expertise and communication skills. Able to quickly adapt to various technical and organizational environments;
Demonstrated ability to maintain quality service by establishing, monitoring, and enforcing organizational standards, as well as defining project requirements and resolving operational problems;
Ability to work well in an international environment.
